01:25:39.379 --> 01:25:42.462
If he didn't travel somewhere,
maybe they did. Where did they go?

01:25:42.539 --> 01:25:44.303
Did they post pictures online?

01:25:44.379 --> 01:25:46.620
No, no, no. They wouldn't do that.
They're too smart for that.

01:25:46.699 --> 01:25:48.303
We're looking for extended family.

01:25:48.379 --> 01:25:50.063
Look for extended family.

01:25:50.219 --> 01:25:54.304
Oh, did they hit anybody's Instagram,
Facebook, Hopscotch? Reddit?

01:25:54.379 --> 01:25:55.540
Nope, none.

01:25:55.619 --> 01:25:56.905
Here. Image Looker.

01:25:56.979 --> 01:25:59.220
An uncle in New York.
Borovsky's father

01:25:59.299 --> 01:26:03.190
accessed the account
from his phone four times, right here.

01:26:03.259 --> 01:26:05.387
Put it up on the main screen.
Get it up.

01:26:07.379 --> 01:26:09.143
They're going to hit Manhattan.

01:26:09.539 --> 01:26:10.904
Jesus.

01:26:11.699 --> 01:26:13.667
Our guy never went to New York.

01:26:14.059 --> 01:26:15.823
He had someone scout it for him.

01:26:16.219 --> 01:26:18.028
And they posted the pictures

01:26:18.219 --> 01:26:20.028
so he could plan the attack.

01:26:28.619 --> 01:26:30.269
Wait, wait, stop.

01:26:30.779 --> 01:26:32.110
Back up.

01:26:34.099 --> 01:26:35.464
There, that.

01:26:40.499 --> 01:26:42.183
You know that building?

01:26:42.659 --> 01:26:45.390
- Jack works there. It's Wall Street.
- Oh, Jesus.

01:26:46.099 --> 01:26:48.147
An attack on downtown Manhattan.

01:26:50.579 --> 01:26:51.740
I'd say that'd start a panic.

01:26:58.939 --> 01:27:00.589
Get me Harper.

01:27:00.659 --> 01:27:01.865
Feds just uncovered evidence

01:27:01.939 --> 01:27:04.704
suggesting he camouflaged
a van stolen from work.

01:27:04.779 --> 01:27:06.781
Discarded tags,
auto paint, paint thinner.

01:27:18.979 --> 01:27:20.663
Tire tracks indicate we're looking for

01:27:20.739 --> 01:27:23.709
a Ford Econoline,
white or blue body, long wheel base.

01:27:23.819 --> 01:27:26.550
Tell FBI we can be at the site
in ten minutes.

01:27:26.619 --> 01:27:28.428
Dr. Muller, there's a car
to take you home.

01:27:28.499 --> 01:27:29.500
An agent will stay with you.

01:27:29.619 --> 01:27:31.906
No. Take me to Lennox Hill Hospital.
They might need me.

01:27:31.979 --> 01:27:33.026
If I don't make it back...

01:27:33.139 --> 01:27:35.221
Look. I will see you tonight.
We're having dinner.

01:27:35.299 --> 01:27:37.666
And we're gonna split the check.

01:27:37.739 --> 01:27:40.868
Sir? Excuse me.
The chopper is ready.

01:27:46.859 --> 01:27:48.623
Have you been in one since?

01:27:48.699 --> 01:27:50.588
Don't worry about me.

01:27:51.259 --> 01:27:52.704
I haven't yet.

01:28:22.499 --> 01:28:23.910
Move! Bomb disposal going in!

01:28:24.259 --> 01:28:26.182
- Hold on!
- Get back, get back!

01:28:27.299 --> 01:28:29.779
The market has opened in New York,
Mr. Cherevin.

01:28:29.859 --> 01:28:32.749
Margin calls from creditors
are imminent. Do we sell?

01:28:32.819 --> 01:28:33.866
Not yet.

01:28:34.099 --> 01:28:36.784
Please proceed as directed by officers.

01:28:37.219 --> 01:28:39.108
I repeat, a total evacuation...

01:28:40.539 --> 01:28:41.620
Jesus Christ.

01:28:43.299 --> 01:28:45.347
Emergency vehicles only

01:28:45.419 --> 01:28:47.228
are allowed access
beyond this perimeter.

01:28:50.819 --> 01:28:52.184
Emergency vehicles only...

01:28:52.259 --> 01:28:54.500
We got a dozen ESU trucks
coming in right now.

01:28:54.619 --> 01:28:56.621
I put the alert out
to the FBI and Counterterrorism

01:28:56.699 --> 01:28:59.543
to expand the EBU's search
to a 30-block radius.

01:28:59.619 --> 01:29:01.064
No, this isn't right.

01:29:01.139 --> 01:29:03.301
I repeat, emergency vehicles only

01:29:03.419 --> 01:29:06.229
are allowed access
beyond this perimeter.

01:29:22.419 --> 01:29:24.660
I want air traffic shut down
over the city.

01:29:27.179 --> 01:29:29.102
Emergency vehicles only

01:29:29.179 --> 01:29:31.181
are allowed access
beyond this perimeter.

01:29:42.779 --> 01:29:43.780
Harper!

01:29:44.019 --> 01:29:45.259
Harper!

01:29:47.259 --> 01:29:48.545
Harper!

01:29:51.619 --> 01:29:52.780
Teddy!

01:29:53.419 --> 01:29:55.148
- Teddy.
- Jack! I thought you were in Moscow.

01:29:55.219 --> 01:29:56.630
I was. I need the bike.

01:29:56.699 --> 01:29:57.780
Jack!

01:29:59.739 --> 01:30:02.265
We recommend immediate
execution of sell orders.

01:30:02.339 --> 01:30:03.340
Wait.

01:30:14.139 --> 01:30:15.300
Jack.

01:30:15.459 --> 01:30:17.029
- I got him!
- Jack, where are you?

01:30:17.099 --> 01:30:18.100
It's a diversion!

01:30:18.179 --> 01:30:19.305
The painting in Cherevin's office,

01:30:19.379 --> 01:30:21.859
it's right out of Napoleon's playbook.
It's Waterloo!

01:30:21.939 --> 01:30:23.703
He's not going to the building,

01:30:23.779 --> 01:30:24.826
he's going under it!

01:30:26.139 --> 01:30:27.140
Jack?

01:30:39.659 --> 01:30:40.660
Jack!

01:30:41.659 --> 01:30:44.539
I need a cross-section of what's
underneath this building. I need it now.

01:30:59.059 --> 01:31:01.869
The greatest upward blast amplification,
where would it be?

01:31:01.939 --> 01:31:03.429
The convection chimney. Here.

01:31:03.539 --> 01:31:05.303
If the force of the blast
is channeled up through it,

01:31:05.379 --> 01:31:07.866
you're looking at shock over pressure,
six or seven buildings come down.

01:31:07.939 --> 01:31:09.543
Jesus. That's half of Wall Street.

01:31:56.299 --> 01:31:57.710
Let's get this thing up!

01:31:58.739 --> 01:32:00.423
Come on, clear the area!
We got to move!

01:32:00.579 --> 01:32:01.910
Open it.

01:32:02.179 --> 01:32:03.819
Secure the ropes. We're going down!

01:32:33.179 --> 01:32:34.704
Oh, God, no.

01:32:42.459 --> 01:32:44.746
Trading is about to be suspended
in New York.

01:32:45.379 --> 01:32:47.381
Mr. Cherevin, we need to act now.

01:32:48.779 --> 01:32:50.702
Please... Aleksandr.

01:33:25.659 --> 01:33:27.980
Where are you, Jack?
I've got people coming to you!

01:33:35.779 --> 01:33:37.065
We got nothing here, Harper!

01:33:45.619 --> 01:33:46.620
Jack.

01:33:46.699 --> 01:33:49.384
The sell-off's programmed for 9:06,
that's two minutes from now.

01:33:49.459 --> 01:33:51.700
Harper, we're not talking about 10
or 15,000 people.

01:33:51.779 --> 01:33:52.940
More like 100,000.

01:33:53.179 --> 01:33:55.022
Just get me a clear path to the water!

01:33:55.379 --> 01:33:57.029
Head north on Front Street.

01:35:49.379 --> 01:35:51.427
Sorokin wants to meet you now.

01:36:10.259 --> 01:36:12.944
It was always for Russia.

01:36:13.899 --> 01:36:15.060
So is this.

01:37:23.859 --> 01:37:27.068
You didn't pick this life. I did.

01:37:32.619 --> 01:37:34.189
But I picked you.

01:37:37.739 --> 01:37:39.070
I can't even kiss you.

01:37:39.579 --> 01:37:40.819
- Yeah, you can.
- That side?

01:37:40.899 --> 01:37:43.630
- It doesn't hurt that much.
- Really? You sure?

01:37:58.939 --> 01:38:02.182
Commander Harper? Dr. Ryan?
They're ready for you.

01:38:04.099 --> 01:38:06.101
Direct. Clear.

01:38:06.899 --> 01:38:10.540
Concise. If he doesn't ask,
he doesn't want to know.

01:38:10.739 --> 01:38:11.820
Yeah.

01:38:12.779 --> 01:38:14.065
Okay.

01:38:15.819 --> 01:38:19.460
Any way you can get that boy-scout-
on-a-field-trip look off your face?

01:38:19.819 --> 01:38:21.423
Not a chance.

01:38:24.099 --> 01:38:26.306
That's what I like about you.

01:38:32.819 --> 01:38:34.821
Harper, when do you ever sleep?

01:38:34.899 --> 01:38:36.389
You know what, don't answer that.

01:38:36.699 --> 01:38:39.748
I kind of like the idea that you don't.
Let me keep thinking it.

01:38:42.539 --> 01:38:44.143
And what's your name, son?

01:38:44.499 --> 01:38:48.140
Ryan, Mr. President. Jack Ryan.

01:38:51.065 --> 01:38:55.065
